Method Detail

isComplete

public boolean isComplete()
Description copied from interface: JMSCommand
Indicates whether the processing of this JMSCommand is completed.

This is necessary as the JMSCommand.execute() method is expected to run on a different thread to one that created the JMSCommand. Implementations of this method are required to ensure that this method returns false if JMSCommand.execute() has not been called or is still running, and true when it has finished.

Specified by:
isComplete in interface JMSCommand
Returns:
true when JMSCommand.execute() has finished running, false otherwise.

isExecutedOK

public boolean isExecutedOK()
Description copied from interface: JMSCommand
Indicates whether the processing of this JMSCommand was successful.

This only has meaning after the method JMSCommand.execute() has been invoked. Prior to that, the results of invoking this method are not defined.

Specified by:
isExecutedOK in interface JMSCommand
Returns:
true if the command completed execution without problems, false otherwise.

getFault

public HJBException getFault()
Description copied from interface: JMSCommand
Obtains the fault describing the problem that caused execution of this JMSCommand to fail.

This only has meaning after the method JMSCommand.execute() has been invoked if JMSCommand.isExecutedOK() is false. Implementations should return null in all other circumstances.

Specified by:
getFault in interface JMSCommand
Returns:
the exception thrown that caused this JMSCommand to fail

toString

public String toString()

completed

protected void completed()
Use to signal that execution of this JMSCommand is complete. After it is invoked, isComplete() return true.

It is synchronized so that other threads can wait a JMSCommand instance's semaphore, and be woken up when this method is executed.
